    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-24T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5296: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-24T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 24, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 24—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>493. My 480, June 24 [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>], 7 p.m., and subsequent.
                    Following telegram has been received from the Minister: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 23, 11 a.m. I agree that customs at Tientsin should be dealt with
                            as <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> organization but I suggest you tell
                            Department of our views, pointing out that American cargo arriving
                            Shanghai, destined Tientsin, will likely be required to pay two
                            assessments, one at Shanghai, under Shanghai customs notification of
                            June 19, 1930, principal Shanghai papers of June 20th, and one at
                            Tientsin, under <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> authorities.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
